PRESS RELEASE
7 AUGUST 2014
BSP AGAIN RECOGNIZES PSA NSCB-CAR
AS OUTSTANDING INFORMATION PARTNER
The Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas (BSP) recently recognized the Philippine Statistics Authority-National
Statistical Coordination Board in the Cordillera Administrative Region (PSA NSCB-CAR) as one of its
two outstanding stakeholders in CAR for the year 2014. The PSA NSCB-CAR was chosen
outstanding partner as source of information for the Report on Regional Economic Developments.
This is the second time that the office has received such award from the BSP.
The award recognizes
institutions and agencies for
consistently providing vital
information to the BSP that are
necessary in the annual
publication of the Report on
Regional Economic
Developments in the Philippines
(REDP).
Mr. Benjamin Y. Navarro,
Regional Head of PSA NSCB-
CAR, and his staff received the
trophy of recognition from BSP
Monetary Board Member Felipe
M. Medalla, Assistant Governor
Ma. Cyd N. Tuaño-Amador and
Acting Director Tomas J. Cariño, Jr. of the La Union Regional Office (LURO) during the 2014 Awards
Ceremony and Appreciation Lunch for Region I and CAR held on August 5, 2014 at the Convention
Hall, BSP-LURO in San Fernando City.
The criteria for the selection of the awardee for the Source of Information Category were the following:
track record of cooperation (25%), relevance of responses (25%), completeness (25%), and
timeliness of data provision (25%). This year’s other awardee in CAR was Texas Instruments
(Philippines) Inc. for Outstanding Respondent for Inter-Company Accounts.
During this annual event, BSP extends formal recognition and appreciation of the significant support
provided by its partners and stakeholders.
